==English==

==Etymology==
From German ''Ästhetik'' or French ''esthétique'', both from Greek ''αἰσθητική'' ("a perceiver", "a sensitive person")

===Alternative spellings===
*[[æsthetics]]
*[[esthetics]]

===Noun===
'''aesthetics'''
# The [[study]] or [[philosophy]] of [[beauty]].

